<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:47PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT EASTERN STOKES...WESTERN
ROCKINGHAM...SOUTHWESTERN HENRY AND SOUTHEASTERN PATRICK COUNTIES
THROUGH 315 PM EDT...
At 246 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mayodan, moving south at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mayodan...
Madison...
Walnut Cove...
Stoneville...
Sandy Ridge...
Pine Hall...
and Intelligence.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
